ESROM Nyandoro was Mamelodi Sundowns “Kabo Yellow” through and through. He was even nicknamed "Yellowman" in his native Zimbabwe. The Bulawayo-born midfield hardman spent 11 years at Chloorkop and made 203 appearances. He scored nine goals during his time with the Brazilians.  Nyandoro was discovered playing for Zimbabwe Saints Juniors in the under 19 Peter Ndlovu invitational tournament at the age of seventeen years. He was snapped up by Amazulu and he became part of a championship-winning team. He later joined Downs and he won the PSL Club Rookie of the Year award in his first season. Nyandoro retired from football in 2015.